{"by":"mixedbit","id":47765121,"parent":47760764,"text":"An interesting variant of a web phishing attack is to combine the back button hijacking with information that comes from the HTTP referer header. HTTP referer discloses from which website the user is coming from, when the user click the back button, the malicious site can take the user to the site that looks identical (except for the URL), but is attacker controlled.","time":1776171713,"type":"comment"}